0jobs%20in%20years.%20But%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20first%20week%2C%20attitudes%20had%20flipped.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20taking%20the%20cart%20out%20of%20the%20hangar%20into%20a%20safe%20area%20to%20do%20some%20software%20punch-ups%2C%20and%20they%20were%20like%2C%20'Wait%20a%20minute%2C%20where%20are%20you%20going%20with%20that%3F%20We%20need%20to%20use%20that%20now.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22059f3fcf-df95-453b-8d74-16e4f02a103f%5C%22%3EA%20hard%2C%20multi-step%2C%20high-risk%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20wearing%20camouflage%20puts%20a%20cylinder%20into%20the%20side%20of%20an%20aircraft.%20The%20sky%20is%20dark%20overcast%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693c4ba464858d02d216b8a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223535%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaintenance%20practices%20on%20aircraft%20like%20the%20KC-135%20date%20back%20decades.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Cody%20J.%20A.%20Mott%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20tanker%20aircraft%20like%20the%20KC-135%2C%20there's%20a%20hole%20just%20big%20enough%20for%20a%20person%20to%20fit%20through%20under%20the%20wing.%20It's%20the%20access%20point%20for%20the%20fuel%20tanks.%20%26quot%3BYou%20crawl%20up%20there%20and%20you%20contort%20your%20body%20to%20be%20able%20to%20lie%20down%20flat%20and%20then%20put%20your%20feet%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20French%20said.%20Inside%2C%20it%20is%20a%20tight%20space%20with%20lots%20of%20bumps%20and%20edges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workers%20wear%20heavy%20protective%20suits%20to%20guard%20against%20fuel%20exposure%20and%20keep%20sweat%20out%20of%20the%20tanks.%20They%20carry%20a%20flashlight%20and%20breathe%20through%20respirators%20that%20feed%20fresh%20air%20in%20from%20a%20hose%20running%20outside%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20the%20aircraft%2C%20a%20support%20team%20stands%20by.%20One%20person%20runs%20tools%20to%20the%20person%20inside%20the%20tank%20while%20another%20monitors%20for%20any%20hazards%20or%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20need%20something%2C%20sometimes%20you%20just%20have%20to%20peel%20the%20respirator%20back%2C%20like%2C%20'Hey%2C%20I%20need%20this%20extra%20wrench%20that%20I%20forgot%2C'%26quot%3B%20French%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20runner%20will%20grab%20it%20and%20bring%20it%20to%20the%20entry%20point%2C%20screaming%20into%20the%20tank%20or%20pulling%20on%20the%20respirator%20hose%20to%20get%20the%20technician's%20attention.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20really%20deep%20in%20the%20tank%2C%20then%20you%20have%20to%20crawl%20back%20to%20get%20it%20from%20them%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20wait%20there%20for%20them%20to%20bring%20it%2C%20reducing%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20you're%20actually%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20a%20worker%20enters%20the%20aircraft%2C%20they'll%20know%20what%20issues%20they're%20looking%20for.%20A%20broken%20rivet%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20along%20with%20regular%20fuel%20tanker%20maintenance%20to%20keep%20the%20aircraft%20operating.%20But%20sometimes%20they%20adjust%20a%20different%20part%20in%20the%20wrong%20area%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideos-show-nato-fighter-jets-refuel-at-30-000-feet-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erefueling%20aircraft%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20leave%20a%20tool%20inside%20the%20tanker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edouble-checking%20the%20work.%20Steps%20like%20removing%20sealant%2C%20cleaning%2C%20and%20putting%20adhesion%20in%20the%20tank%20require%20approval%20from%20other%20team%20members.%20It's%20inherently%20an%20hourslong%20job%20made%20even%20longer%20by%20wait%20times%20and%20communication%20lags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20if%20it%20all%20runs%20smoothly.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESometimes%2C%20technicians%20make%20mistakes%2C%20extending%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BA%20simple%20sealant%20job%20can%20turn%20from%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20of%20scraping%20and%20then%20eventually%20reapplying%20to%20another%20day%20because%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20you%20applied%20it%20to%20the%20wrong%20spot%2C%26quot%3B%20Tech%20Sgt.%20Chris%20Anderson%2C%20with%20the%20100th%20Air%20Refueling%20Wing%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20that%20we%20did%20things%20left%20a%20lot%20of%20room%20for%20error.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20logical%20fix%2C%20Frank%20said%2C%20was%20something%20wearable%3A%20%26quot%3Ba%20camera%20with%20two-way%20audio%20would%20be%20awesome%2C%20and%20if%20it%20had%20lights%2C%20that'd%20be%20a%20second%20bonus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a2d623cd-1c38-44df-830d-0d8a17f2d384%5C%22%3EA%20new%20way%20of%20doing%20an%20old%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22983%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20pictures%20are%20collaged%20into%20one.%20The%20top%20photo%20shows%20a%20computer%20and%20tablet%20at%20a%20mobile%20workstation%20in%20an%20empty%20white%20warehouse.%20The%20bottom%20left%20photo%20shows%20the%20tablet.%20And%20the%20bottom%20right%20shows%20a%20grey%20headset.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693c4c29832e0ef1ead62423%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22812%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIRIS%20includes%20the%20mobile%20workstation%20and%20the%20headsets%20for%20maintainers.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20MetroStar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IRIS%20technology%20sits%20on%20top%20of%20the%20face%20mask%20tanker%20maintenance%20workers%20wear.%20It%20features%20a%20high-definition%20video%20camera%2C%20a%20two-way%20comms%20system%20that%20goes%20inside%20the%20mask%2C%20and%20a%20hands-free%20light.%20IRIS%20shows%20everything%20the%20technician%20is%20looking%20at%20to%20those%20outside%20the%20fuel%20tank%20and%20allows%20them%20to%20communicate%20with%20their%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20connects%20to%20a%20mobile%20workstation%20outside%20the%20aircraft.%20On%20the%20cart%2C%20which%20can%20host%20up%20to%20four%20IRIS%20units%20simultaneously%2C%20the%20support%20team%20can%20see%20what%20the%20technician%20sees%2C%20talk%20them%20through%20the%20work%2C%20and%20record%20the%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVideo%20records%20help%20verify%20what%20each%20shift%20completed%20and%20resolve%20disputes%20quickly.%20For%20instance%2C%20Anderson%20said%20that%20the%20day%20shift%20had%20cleared%20a%20fuel%20puddle%2C%20but%20the%20next%20shift%20found%20one%20and%20questioned%20the%20work.%20IRIS%20showed%20that%20the%20first%20team%20had%20done%20the%20job%2C%20revealing%2C%20as%20French%20said%2C%20%26quot%3B%20another%20problem%2C%20something's%20leaking.%26quot%3B%20That%20prevented%20unnecessary%20rework%20and%20let%20them%20fix%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20a%20tricky%20aircraft%20issue%20could%20halt%20work%20while%20the%20right%20Air%20Force%20experts%20traveled%20in%20to%20assess%20it.%20Now%2C%20IRIS%20can%20send%20video%20to%20them%20instantly%20or%20launch%20a%20group%20call%20so%20everyone%20can%20see%20exactly%20what%20the%20technician%20sees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevelopers%20also%20see%20AI%20playing%20a%20growing%20role%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnavy-ai-cut-hourslong-submarine-planning-job-to-minutes-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estreamlining%20the%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20a%20technician%20uses%20IRIS%2C%20an%20AI%20agent%20compiles%20images%20and%20data%20to%20make%20requests%2C%20anticipate%20needed%20work%2C%20and%20handle%20forms.%20That%20frees%20technicians%20from%20what%20retired%20Air%20Force%20Maj.%20Gen.%20Cedric%20George%20called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-special-forces-using-lot-of-ai-for-cognitive-load-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshallow%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20when%20their%20shift%20ends%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20he%20or%20she%20has%20to%20do%20is%20button%20up%2C%20clean%20up%2C%20go%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIRIS%20is%20currently%20in%20use%20only%20at%20Mildenhall%2C%C2%A0but%20early%20results%20are%20promising%2C%20as%20the%20Air%20Force%20considers%20expanding%20it%20to%20other%20bases.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETechnicians%20using%20the%20system%20haven't%20had%20any%20safety%20incidents%2C%20and%20inspections%20are%20running%2060%25%20faster%20in%20test%20environments%2C%20according%20to%20pilot%20evaluations%20and%20internal%20logs.%20Based%20on%20KC-135%20maintenance%20baselines%2C%20MetroStar%20estimates%20IRIS%20could%20save%2035%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-techs-strip-parts-fighter-jets-subs-cannibalize-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emaintainer%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20add%20more%20than%207%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ff-35-stealth-fighter-deliveries-have-been-falling-behind-watchdog-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaircraft%20availability%20days%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20attributed%20the%20success%20of%20IRIS%20to%20the%20technicians%20who%20wanted%20to%20revamp%20the%20decades-old%20process%20to%20make%20it%20better%20for%20future%20workers.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20for%20the%20faint%20of%20heart%2C%20it's%20dirty%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20saying%20current%20technicians%20who%20worked%20on%20IRIS%20believe%20future%20maintainers%20%26quot%3Bhave%20to%20have%20something%20better%20than%20what%20we%20have%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbehind-new-tech-making-dirty-hard-air-force-job-easier-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765801621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbehind-new-tech-making-dirty-hard-air-force-job-easier-