0company%20an%20edge%20over%20its%20rivals.%20After%20months%20of%20a%20cultural%20reset%20in%20early%202025%2C%20employee%20sentiment%20improved%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20a%20Meta%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20citing%20a%20recent%20internal%20employee%20sentiment%20questionnaire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20are%20worried%20about%20the%20company's%20strategy%2C%20particularly%20its%20plan%20to%20sink%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20into%20AI%20infrastructure%20and%20talent.%20The%20question%20is%20whether%20Meta%20is%20overdoing%20it.%20Shares%20have%20risen%207.5%25%20this%20year%2C%20less%20than%20half%20that%20of%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%2C%20and%20have%20underperformed%20most%20of%20the%20so-called%20Magnificent%207%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20company%20must%20articulate%20its%20vision%2C%20show%20how%20its%20pieces%20fit%20together%2C%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20demonstrate%20steady%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mike%20Proulx%2C%20research%20director%20at%20Forrester%2C%20who%20covers%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20account%20of%20Meta's%20%26quot%3Byear%20of%20intensity%26quot%3B%20is%20based%20on%20interviews%20conducted%20by%20Business%20Insider%20with%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20current%20and%20former%20employees%2C%20analysts%2C%20and%20academic%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-business%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInside%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E%20stories%20reveal%20the%20inner%20workings%20of%20companies%20from%20Silicon%20Valley%20to%20Wall%20Street%20that%20are%20shaping%20our%20world%20today.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Finside-business%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESign%20up%20for%20the%20newsletter.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283e53053-7a7a-4815-9bef-2e0beffbdcd9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20AI%20overhaul%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20summer%2C%20Zuckerberg%20sought%20to%20change%20the%20perception%20that%20Meta%20was%20trailing%20behind%20its%20AI%20rivals.%20In%20June%2C%20the%20company%20made%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scale-ai-15-billion-alexandr-wang-acquihire-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2414%20billion%20investment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20AI%20training%20company%20Scale%20AI%20and%20hired%20its%2028-year-old%20founder%2C%20Alexandr%20Wang%2C%20as%20chief%20AI%20officer.%20Two%20months%20later%2C%20it%20rebranded%20its%20team%20focused%20on%20AI%20efforts%20to%20Meta%20Superintelligence%20Labs%20(MSL).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Meta's%20leadership%20sought%20to%20reorganize%20teams%20and%20recruit%20top%20talent%20from%20competitors%2C%20some%20ex-employees%20went%20public%20with%20the%20view%20that%20the%20company%20lacked%20a%20coherent%20AI%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoena%20Zhang%2C%20a%20former%20Meta%20Superintelligence%20Labs%20employee%2C%20said%20in%20a%20November%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fjiezhang-joena_episode-decision-why-activity-7399360427224129536-oFda%3Futm_source%3Dshare%26utm_medium%3Dmember_desktop%26rcm%3DACoAACqwxRcBBmz-yNxjii4UEH1xFGKSZgcfU0c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bnobody%20really%20knew%20what%20anyone%20was%20doing%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%20at%20MSL%20%E2%80%94%20then%20called%20GenAI.%20She%20said%20there%20were%20%26quot%3Bendless%26quot%3B%20meetings%20that%20didn't%20result%20in%20%26quot%3Bactual%20decisions.%26quot%3B%20And%20in%20a%20July%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblankevoort.substack.com%2Fp%2Fmetas-ai-culture%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESubstack%3C%2Fa%3E%20post%2C%20former%20Meta%20researcher%20Tijmen%20Blankevoort%20wrote%20that%20Meta%20had%20%26quot%3Ba%20wavering%20vision%20that%20was%20tough%20for%20team%20members%20to%20enthusiastically%20rally%20behind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20began%20offering%20massive%20compensation%20packages%20to%20attract%20top%20AI%20talent%20from%20rival%20labs%2C%20including%20OpenAI%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-superintelligence-team-hires-deepmind-scale-ai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20AI%20division%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20DeepMind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20created%20rifts%20between%20the%20%26quot%3Bold%20guard%26quot%3B%20and%20newer%20hires%20by%20offering%20outsiders%20significantly%20more%20compensation%20than%20existing%20employees%20got.%20It%20fueled%20a%20quiet%20competition%20to%20prove%20whose%20ideas%20for%20AI%20features%20were%20more%20valuable%2C%20according%20to%20two%20MSL%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tensions%20also%20revolved%20around%20access%20to%20computing%20resources%20and%20the%20prestige%20of%20being%20associated%20with%20the%20elite%20team%20at%20the%20center%20of%20MSL%2C%20as%20one%20researcher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-talent-war-superintelligence-push-tension-desertion-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20Meta%20undertook%20its%20fourth%20major%20reorganization%20in%20six%20months%20to%20streamline%20its%20AI%20efforts%2C%20dividing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-superintelligence-labs-reorg-alexandr-wang-memo-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMSL%20into%20four%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20a%20new%20TBD%20Lab%20(short%20for%20%26quot%3Bto%20be%20determined%26quot%3B)%2C%20a%20product%20team%20overseeing%20the%20Meta%20AI%20assistant%2C%20an%20infrastructure%20team%2C%20and%20the%20company's%20long-standing%20Fundamental%20AI%20Research%20(FAIR)%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20shake-up%2C%20it%20was%20unclear%20who%20owned%20which%20projects%2C%20and%20people%20were%20reassigned%20between%20teams%2C%20according%20to%20the%20two%20MSL%20employees%2C%20one%20of%20whom%20added%20that%20the%20flow%20of%20information%20between%20TBD%20and%20MSL%20wasn't%20always%20even.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alex%20Wang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f91050599d46a4ccc0a471%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlexandr%20Wang%20shared%20a%20memo%20announcing%20job%20cuts.%3Cp%3ETaylor%20Hill%2FFilmMagic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20internal%20shake-up%2C%20a%20Meta%20spokesperson%20pointed%20Business%20Insider%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fandymstone%2Fstatus%2F1957894385179185484%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20X%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Andy%20Stone%2C%20a%20Meta%20communications%20executive%2C%20describing%20previous%20reporting%20about%20the%20company's%20AI%20restructuring%20as%20%26quot%3Bnavelgazing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20eight%20of%20Meta's%20AI%20staffers%2C%20including%20researchers%2C%20engineers%2C%20and%20a%20senior%20product%20leader%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-superintelligence-team-researchers-exit-ai-push-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleft%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20two%20months%20of%20MSL's%20formation.%20Meta%20said%20most%20had%20been%20with%20the%20company%20for%20years%2C%20and%20that%20some%20attrition%20is%20normal%20for%20an%20organization%20of%20its%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20after%20the%20August%20shuffle%2C%20Meta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falexandr-wang-meta-superintelligence-labs-layoffs-memo-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20about%20600%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20a%20wider%20reorganization%20of%20the%20MSL%20division.%20Wang%20told%20employees%20that%20the%20cuts%20were%20designed%20to%20speed%20up%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShay%20Boloor%2C%20chief%20market%20strategist%20at%20Futurum%20Equities%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20changes%20have%20helped%20Meta%20move%20faster%20in%20model%20releases%20and%20in%20integrating%20its%20AI%20across%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20WhatsApp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMeta%20is%20now%20one%20of%20the%20only%20companies%20training%20frontier-class%20models%20and%20deploying%20them%20to%20billions%20of%20users%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20where%20I%20want%20it%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-cto-andrew-bosworth-reshuffling-metaverse-unit-read-the-memo-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshook%20up%20its%20leadership%20ranks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Reality%20Labs%2C%20the%20division%20responsible%20for%20developing%20its%20virtual%20and%20mixed%20reality%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-job-cuts-metaverse-reality-labs-ai-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsidering%20budget%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20metaverse%20unit%20that%20sits%20within%20Reality%20Labs%2C%20which%20could%20result%20in%20job%20cuts%2C%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20A%20Meta%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20it%20is%20reallocating%20some%20of%20its%20investment%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20Metaverse%20toward%20AI%20glasses%20and%20wearables%26quot%3B%20to%20match%20momentum%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bwasn't%20planning%20any%20broader%20changes%20than%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f48ff22-3cfe-4c28-8ec8-141879596f3a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Intense'%20performance%20reviews%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MSL%20layoffs%20were%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20effort%20by%20Meta%20to%20tighten%20operational%20efficiency%20this%20year%2C%20as%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-why-companies-laying-off-managers-flattening-org-structure-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduced%20layers%20of%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20implemented%20a%20stricter%20performance%20review%20process%20than%20in%20previous%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20told%20employees%20in%20January%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bdecided%20to%20raise%20the%20bar%20on%20performance%20management%26quot%3B%20and%20would%20move%20quickly%20to%20cut%20about%205%25%20of%20%26quot%3Blow%20performers.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%20cut%20about%203%2C600%20jobs%20in%20February%20from%20its%20workforce%20of%20about%2078%2C450%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20May%2C%20it%20directed%20managers%20to%20place%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finternal-memo-meta-increases-employees-rated-below-expectations-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20proportion%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20employees%20in%20its%20bottom%20review%20rankings%3A%20For%20teams%20of%20150%20or%20more%2C%2015%25%20to%2020%25%20of%20employees%20should%20be%20rated%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bbelow%20expectations%26quot%3B%20tier%2C%20compared%20with%2012%25%20to%2015%25%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20employees%20said%20the%20revised%20system%20created%20a%20pressure-cooker%20environment%20and%20encouraged%20more%20cutthroat%20competition%20between%20staff.%20Managers%20and%20employees%20described%20a%20shift%20toward%20short-term%20projects%20as%20teams%20looked%20to%20protect%20themselves%20from%20landing%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20ranking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20requirement%20to%20place%20more%20staff%20in%20lower%20performance%20tiers%20saw%20some%20managers%20strategically%20leave%20positions%20open%20or%20hire%20employees%20solely%20to%20place%20them%20in%20the%20bottom%20tier%2C%20two%20managers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20says%20employee%20sentiment%20improved%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year.%20Its%20latest%20internal%20employee%20sentiment%20questionnaire%2C%20which%20ran%20from%20October%2020%20to%20November%203%2C%20showed%20%26quot%3Boptimism%26quot%3B%20rose%20to%2080%25%2C%20%26quot%3Bpride%26quot%3B%20at%2071%25%20and%20%26quot%3Bconfidence%20in%20leadership%26quot%3B%20at%2068%25%2C%20according%20to%20data%20Meta%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20those%20metrics%20was%20up%20between%2010%20and%2012%20percentage%20points%20compared%20to%20the%20last%20survey%2C%20which%20ran%20April%2021%20through%20May%205%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20The%20latest%20survey%20had%20a%2091%25%20participation%20rate%2C%20Meta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da9a7e2e-6e09-4d5b-a1bb-faca6f6daccd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDepartures%20and%20loyalists%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20combination%20of%20policy%20shifts%2C%20reorganizations%2C%20job%20cuts%2C%20and%20stricter%20performance%20expectations%20triggered%20a%20wave%20of%20departures%20in%202025%2C%20according%20to%20five%20internal%20farewell%20posts%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20Some%20employees%20said%20Meta's%20evolving%20political%20posture%20and%20internal%20governance%20changes%20no%20longer%20aligned%20with%20their%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMeta%20in%202025%20is%20a%20very%20different%20company%20from%20what%20Oculus%20%26amp%3B%20Facebook%20were%20in%202017%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20engineer%2C%20who%20left%20Meta%20in%20August%20after%20nearly%20eight%20years%20at%20the%20company%2C%20wrote%20in%20an%20internal%20farewell%20message%2C%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20These%20types%20of%20notes%20are%20known%20internally%20as%20%26quot%3Bbadge%20posts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cited%20a%20%26quot%3Bmatter%20of%20principles%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20departure%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bsometimes%20implicit%2C%20sometimes%20explicit%20alignment%20with%20the%20new%20US%20government%26quot%3B%20clashed%20with%20his%20personal%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222653%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20speaks%20on%20stage%20in%20front%20of%20a%20screen%20that%20says%20Meta%20Connect%202025%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6900f4c2c007ca8c2737c6b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221769%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20speaks%20at%20the%202025%20Meta%20Connect%20conference%20in%20Menlo%20Park%2C%20California%2C%20on%20September%2017%2C%202025.%3Cp%3EBENJAMIN%20LEGENDRE%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20themes%20surfaced%20in%20other%20employee%20departures%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20unnecessary%20pressure%2C%20lack%20of%20empathy%2C%20and%20occasional%20lack%20of%20fairness%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20wrote%20in%20another%20farewell%20post%20from%20January%2C%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFighting%20for%20scope.%20Narratives.%20Oh%2C%20the%20narratives%20-%20I'm%20so%20looking%20forward%20to%20not%20hearing%20that%20word%20for%20a%20while.%20Smart%20and%20kind%20people%20bending%20their%20values%20to%20survive%20because%20they've%20been%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20their%20seats%20for%20too%20long.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20resignations%20represent%20a%20small%20slice%20of%20the%20company.%20Meta%20has%2078%2C450%20employees%2C%20and%20head%20count%20is%20up%208%25%20year-over-year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20departing%20employees%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they%20no%20longer%20had%20a%20meaningful%20outlet%20to%20share%20feedback%20with%20leadership%20on%20topics%20such%20as%20DEI%20and%20embracing%20%26quot%3Bmasculine%20energy%26quot%3B%20because%20questions%20for%20Q%26amp%3BA%20sessions%20were%20preselected%2C%20and%20that%20posts%20critical%20of%20leadership%20decisions%20we