0it%20once%20did%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20Trump%20administration%20agrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%20concluded%20its%20negotiations%20on%20the%20Workforce%20Pell%20program%20on%20December%2012%2C%20a%20new%20initiative%20included%20in%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20%26quot%3Bbig%20beautiful%26quot%3B%20spending%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20would%20extend%20Pell%20grants%20to%20low-income%20borrowers%20in%20short-term%20certification%20programs%2C%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20providing%20more%20funding%20for%20alternative%20paths%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-no-college-degree-makes-six-figures-no-regrets-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efour-year%20college%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20trade%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicholas%20Kent%2C%20the%20department's%20undersecretary%2C%20acknowledged%20during%20remarks%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20negotiations%20that%20a%20standard%20four-year%20college%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-high-schools-changing-value-of-college-trade-higher-education-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edegree%20is%20losing%20its%20value%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmericans%20are%20questioning%20whether%20the%20value%20of%20higher%20education%20is%20worth%20the%20cost.%20Polling%20also%20shows%20that%20students%20do%20not%20believe%20they%20are%20graduating%20with%20the%20specific%20skills%20that%20they%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Kent%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-value-of-college-higher-education-student-debt-tuition-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eskepticism%20about%20college%20degrees%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20led%20to%20students%20%26quot%3Bshowing%20more%20interest%20in%20pathways%20that%20get%20them%20into%20the%20labor%20force%20more%20quickly%20and%20without%20unnecessary%20debt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollege%20still%20remains%20the%20primary%20path%20in%20the%20US%20for%20postsecondary%20education%2C%20and%20recent%20data%20from%20the%20New%20York%20Federal%20Reserve%20showed%20that%20it%20continues%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-a-college-degree-worth-it-majors-completion-living-costs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elead%20to%20higher%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20addition%2C%20proponents%20argue%20the%20value%20of%20college%20extends%20beyond%20earnings%20to%20social%20opportunities%20and%20exposure%20to%20new%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-officially-ends-save-plan-student-loan-borrowers-resume-payments-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigh%20student%20debt%20loads%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20jobs%20eliminating%20degree%20requirements%20have%20sparked%20a%20growing%20interest%20in%20short-term%20credential%20programs%20and%20the%20trades%2C%20which%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20attempting%20to%20boost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Madaio%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20at%20the%20nonprofit%20The%20Institute%20for%20College%20Access%20and%20Success%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20with%20more%20Pell%20grant%20support%20extended%20to%20short-term%20programs%2C%20it's%20likely%20that%20more%20schools%20will%20offer%20them%20and%20more%20students%20will%20enroll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20all%20ensuring%20that%20students%20take%20what's%20right%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Madaio%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20programs%20should%20pay%20off%20for%20students%2C%20and%20they%20should%20give%20a%20good%20value%20and%20use%20students'%20limited%20lifetime%20Pell%20grant%20eligibility%20for%20something%20that's%20going%20to%20work%20for%20them%20and%20potentially%20allow%20them%20to%20get%20a%20job%20later%20down%20the%20road.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe27218e-a729-4b23-8a3a-e5c833eaacee%5C%22%3EStrengthening%20the%20college%20and%20non-college%20paths%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education's%20Workforce%20Pell%20proposal%20will%20have%20a%20period%20of%20public%20comment%20before%20it%20is%20set%20to%20be%20implemented%20in%20July%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20rule%20is%20implemented%20as%20proposed%2C%20eligibility%20guidelines%20would%20vary%20by%20state.%20According%20to%20the%20department%2C%20each%20state%20will%20determine%20what%20qualifies%20as%20a%20high-skill%2C%20high-wage%2C%20or%20in-demand%20job%20based%20on%20what%20aligns%20with%20the%20industry%20needs%20in%20that%20state.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20state%20where%20agriculture%20dominates%20the%20economy%20might%20choose%20to%20prioritize%20short-term%20programs%20in%20that%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMadaio%20said%20that%20this%20state%20variance%20is%20by%20design%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20important%20that%20states%20are%20taking%20a%20close%20look%20at%20what%20they're%20approving%20to%20ensure%20that%20there%20are%20jobs%20in%20that%20state%20and%20that%20these%20are%20valuable%20workforce%20training%20programs%20for%20jobs%20that%20are%20needed%20in%20that%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccountability%20is%20key%20here%2C%20Madaio%20said%2C%20and%20states%20should%20ensure%20that%20schools%20are%20delivering%20on%20the%20value%20of%20the%20programs%20they%20offer.%20Otherwise%2C%20students%20could%20be%20left%20paying%20off%20loans%20they%20cannot%20afford%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20something%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-new-gainful-employment-rule-student-loan-debt-relief-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20gainful%20employment%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20the%20department%20is%20set%20to%20negotiate%20in%20January%2C%20will%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20really%20positive%20developments%20that%20show%20that%20there's%20a%20broad%20agreement%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20that%20we%20owe