tps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-dictionary-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evibe%20coding%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%202025%20word%20of%20the%20year.%20Coined%20by%20OpenAI%20cofounder%20Andrej%20Karpathy%20in%20February%2C%20the%20term%20refers%20to%20using%20language%20and%20generative%20AI%20to%20speed%20up%20the%20coding%20process.%20Soon%20after%2C%20companies%20were%20adding%20it%20as%20a%20desired%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-tech-firms-hire-engineers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskill%20in%20job%20listings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVibe%20coding%20was%20the%20catalyst%20for%20the%20sort%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-vibe-working-coding-microsoft-openai-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evibe%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20era%20we've%20entered.%20It's%20a%20shift%20in%20how%20people%20think%20about%20their%20roles%20and%20relationships%20to%20work%20amid%20an%20AI%20boom%2C%20and%20software%20engineering%2C%20long%20considered%20a%20stable%20and%20lucrative%20career%20path%2C%20has%20perhaps%20been%20the%20career%20most%20scrutinized%20and%20pushed%20down%20a%20path%20toward%20automation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproduct-managers-rule-silicon-valley-tech-industry-programmers-jobs-ceo-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProduct%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20suggested%20that%20AI%20will%20supercharge%20them%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20take%20on%20some%20technical%20coding%20tasks%20and%20work%20without%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExecs%20have%20been%20all-in%3A%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20said%20he%20expected%20AI%20to%20write%20half%20of%20Meta's%20code%20within%20a%20year%3B%20this%20spring%2C%20AI%20was%20already%20doing%20about%20a%20third%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-code-meta-microsoft-google-llamacon-engineers-2025-4%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAI%2520Now%2520Writes%2520a%2520Big%2CMicrosoft%2520and%2520Google%2520%252D%2520Business%2520Insider%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecode%20at%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20on%20some%20Microsoft%20projects.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-ai-90-percent-code-3-to-6-months-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%3C%2Fa%3E%20predicted%20in%20March%20that%2090%25%20of%20code%20would%20be%20generated%20by%20AI%20in%20three%20to%20six%20months.%20The%20bullish%20estimate%20hasn't%20materialized%20for%20most%2C%20but%20Amodei%20said%20in%20October%20the%20company's%20AI%20tool%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-anthropic-teams-coding-with-claude-ai-not-replacing-humans-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClaude%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20writing%20most%20of%20the%20code%20at%20Anthropic.%20Cognition%2C%20which%20built%20an%20AI-powered%20software%20engineer%20it%20named%20Devin%2C%20is%20now%20valued%20at%20%2410%20billion.%20Some%20without%20computer%20science%20backgrounds%20or%20any%20training%20in%20coding%20are%20vibe%20coding%20their%20own%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVibe%20coding%20isn't%20yet%20the%20miracle%20that%20AI%20evangelists%20have%20professed.%20AI-generated%20code%20can%20have%20sneaky%20errors%20that%20pose%20security%20risks.%20As%20it%20takes%20on%20the%20work%20of%20junior%20developers%2C%20companies%20eager%20for%20gain%20could%20displace%20humans.%20Time%20banked%20with%20shortcuts%20now%20could%20disrupt%20training%20ground%20for%20learning%20basic%20coding%20skills%2C%20creating%20a%20tech%20worker%20career%20ladder%20collapse%20could%20ricochet%20through%20the%20industry.%20There%20is%20potential%20for%20developers%20to%20save%20time%2C%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20learn%20new%20languages%20and%20skills%20(something%20Raja%20tells%20me%20he's%20done)%2C%20and%20to%20pare%20down%20their%20technical%20debt%2C%20or%20code%20that%20needs%20maintenance.%20But%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20the%20industry%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20it%20is%20a%20silver%20bullet%20to%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20were%20dealing%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20optimism%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20magical%20thinking%26quot%3B%20around%20the%20capabilities%20of%20AI%2C%20says%20Tariq%20Shaukat%2C%20CEO%20of%20Sonar%2C%20a%20company%20that%20provides%20developers%20with%20tools%20to%20verify%20code.%20%26quot%3BThe%20vibe%20engineering%20tools%20are%20producing%20a%20lot%20of%20quantity.%20It's%20getting%20more%20functionally%20correct%2C%20but%20it's%20actually%20becoming%20more%20difficult%20to%20determine%20the%20quality%20and%20get%20the%20level%20of%20trust%20that%20you%20need%20to%20integrate%20that%20into%20your%20code%20base.%26quot%3B%20The%20ranks%20of%20AI%20holdouts%20among%20developers%20are%20shrinking.%20A%202025%20survey%20of%20professional%20developers%20from%20Stack%20Overflow%20found%20that%20only%2019.3%25%20don't%20use%20AI%2C%20and%20a%20commensurate%2019.7%25%20have%20an%20unfavorable%20opinion%20of%20AI.%20Yet%20less%20than%203%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20highly%20trust%20AI%20for%20accuracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20has%20asked%20a%20chatbot%20a%20question%20knows%20that%20even%20a%20short%20inquiry%20often%20results%20in%20a%20verbose%20response.%20The%20same%20is%20true%20of%20code%20%E2%80%94%20when%20AI%20generates%20it%2C%20it's%20typically%20longer%2C%20making%20the%20possibility%20of%20errors%20hiding%20in%20the%20code%20more%20likely.%20Amy%20Carrillo%20Cotten%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20customer%20transformation%20at%20software%20development%20company%20Uplevel%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkslop-oozing-americas-white-collar-offices-generative-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%3A%20%26quot%3BFor%20a%20lot%20of%20engineers%2C%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20looks%20different%20is%20where%20they%20spend%20their%20time%2C%20not%20exactly%20how%20much%20time%20it%20took.%26quot%3B%20Uplevel%20studied%20800%20software%20developers%20last%20year%20and%20compared%20the%20productivity%20levels%20of%20those%20who%20used%20GitHub's%20Copilot%20to%20those%20who%20did%20not.%20The%20developers%20who%20used%20Copilot%20weren't%20more%20efficient%20or%20less%20burnt%20out%2C%20and%20their%20code%20had%20bugs%20in%20it%2041%25%20more%20frequently.%20(GitHub's%20own%20research%20found%20that%20those%20who%20used%20Copilot%20wrote%20about%2018%20lines%20of%20clean%20code%2C%20compared%20to%2016%20lines%20for%20those%20who%20didn't.)%20For%20many%2C%20that%20shift%20from%20writing%20to%20reviewing%20code%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20the%20job%20they%20signed%20up%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Shaukat%20says%2C%20which%20brings%20a%20big%20adjustment%20for%20many%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20job%20looks%20completely%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Frank%20Fusco%2C%20CEO%20of%20a%20software%20company%20called%20Silicon%20Society.%20His%20company%20works%20with%20clients%20on%20their%20software%2C%20but%20now%20they%20often%20get%20amateur%2C%20vibe%20coded%20versions%20of%20those%20ideas%20as%20the%20starting%20point.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20would%20normally%20do%20in%20code%20that%20would%20take%20me%20days%2C%20I%20now%20do%20in%20words%20and%20it%20takes%20me%20hours.%26quot%3B%20But%20Fusco%20tells%20me%20he%20worries%20about%20a%20decline%20in%20critical%20thinking%20and%20basic%20coding%20skills.%20We're%20%26quot%3Bhardwired%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20to%20find%20%26quot%3Bthe%20shortest%20path%20to%20the%20solution.%26quot%3B%20But%20that%20approach%20isn't%20the%20best%20for%20sharpening%20coding%20skills.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20is%20a%20muscle%20that%20you%20have%20to%20work%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20tricky%20to%20say%20AI%20is%20already%20killing%20developer%20jobs.%20Years%20of%20layoffs%20and%20%26quot%3Bright-sizing%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20paired%20with%20the%20economic%20precarity%20that%20has%20also%20defined%202025%2C%20could%20be%20shifting%20industry%20roles%20alongside%20AI.%20As%20of%20November%2C%20there%20were%20about%2092%2C500%20active%20job%20postings%20seeking%20software%20engineers%2C%20down%20from%20nearly%20102%2C000%20last%20November%20and%20159%2C000%20at%20the%20start%20of%202023%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20CompTIA%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20trade%20association%20for%20the%20US%20IT%20industry.%20The%20number%20of%20active%20tech%20job%20posts%20overall%20has%20fallen%2C%20from%20621%2C000%20in%20early%202023%20to%20433%2C500%20last%20month.%20But%20the%20proportion%20of%20open%20jobs%20looking%20for%20AI%20skills%20has%20jumped%20by%2053%25%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20decades%20of%20being%20told%20to%20pursue%20computer%20science%20as%20a%20stable%20career%20and%20a%20proliferation%20of%20coding%20bootcamps%2C%20working%20as%20a%20developer%20may%20not%20be%20as%20cushy.%20College%20seniors%20studying%20computer%20science%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20any%20other%20discipline%20to%20say%20they're%20%26quot%3Bvery%20pessimistic%26quot%3B%20about%20their%20careers%2C%20according%20to%20a%202025%20survey%20from%20early%20career%20website%20Handshake.%20They're%20the%20group%20most%20likely%20to%20say%20the%20advances%20of%20generative%20AI%20have%20made%20them%20regret%20their%20major%20choice.%20But%20young%20people%20are%20divided%20%E2%80%94%2043%25%20of%20computer%20science%20majors%20said%20they%20think%20AI%20will%20have%20a%20positive%20effect%20on%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAutomation%20is%20in%20some%20ways%20marking%20%26quot%3Ba%20correction%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20developer%20labor%20market%2C%20says%20April%20Schuppel%2C%20developer%20relations%20manager%20at%20software%20company%20Apryse.%20Before%20AI%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20needed%20as%20many%20people%20who%20were%20really%20pushing%20out%20the%20code%20to%20take%20the%20ideas%20of%20the%20visionaries%20and%20bring%20them%20to%20life.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20people%20who%20have%20always%20been%20able%20to%20make%20the%20most%20impact%2C%20they're%20still%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20the%20safest.%26quot%3B%20Developers%20who%20looked%20at%20their%20jobs%20as%20clearing%20tickets%20might%20be%20more%20replaceable%20than%20those%20who%20were%20creative%20and%20cared%20about%20the%20project%20from%20start%20to%20finish.%20We're%20far%20from%20realizing%20the%20end%20game%20of%20vibe%20coding%2C%20but%20for%20creative%2C%20forward-thinking%20developers%2C%20there's%20optimism%20for%20now.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20well-rounded%20people%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20going%20to%20have%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20Schuppel%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20could%20bring%20more%20opportunity%20for%20software%20testers%2C%20and%20also%20help%20companies%20pare%20down%20their%20technical%20debt.%20The%20developer%20job%20market%20might%20look%20messy%20right%20now%2C%20but%20there's%20still%20a%20heavy%20focus%20on%20the%20human%20aspect%20of%20the%20career%20than%20in%20the%20picture%20painted%20by%20some%20Big%20Tech%20execs.%20%26quot%3BIf%20there%20are%20opportunities%20for%20more%20fine-tuned%20models%2C%20more%20specialized%20models%20that%20only%20do%20certain%20types%20of%20code%20updates%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20way%20to%20use%20that%20more%20to%20augment%20human%20developers%20as%20opposed%20to%20replace%2C%20that%20seems%20like%20that's%20where%20this%20is%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Tim%20Herbert%2C%20chief%20research%20officer%20at%20CompTIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECodebases%20are%20valuable%2C%20and%20the%20security%20risks%20posed%20by%20goofs%20in%20AI%20code%20are%20serious%20threats.%20Traffic%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-vibe-coding-tools-traffic-plunge-summer-arr-hype-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evibe%20coding%20sites%3C%2Fa%3E%20slumped%20in%20September%20after%20a%20summer%20of%20hype.%20Even%20Karpathy%20said%20his%20latest%20project%20is%20%26quot%3Bbasically%20entirely%20hand-written%20(with%20tab%20autocomplete)%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20post%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fkarpathy%2Fstatus%2F1977758204139331904%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20tried%20to%20use%20claude%2Fcodex%20agents%20a%20few%20times%20but%20they%20just%20didn't%20work%20well%20enough%20at%20all%20and%20net%20unhelpful.%26quot%3B%20If%202025%20was%20the%20year%20tech%20companies%20went%20all%20in%20on%20AI%2C%202026%20might%20be%20the%20year%20when%20some%20of%20the%20craze%20around%20vibe%20coding%20subsides%20and%20reality%20sets%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyear-coding-changed-forever-silicon-valley-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765789861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693c9685832e0ef1ead62dca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyear-coding-changed-forever-silicon-valley-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Optimism%2C%20laziness%2C%20and%20magical%20thinking%3A%20The%20year%20vibe%20coding%20took%20over%20tech.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyear-coding-changed-forever-silicon-valley-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUr