s%20year's%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20a%20new%20global%20survey%20says%20the%20technology%20could%20fuel%20a%20rebound%20in%20some%20entry-level%20hiring%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic-company%20CEOs%20say%20AI%20is%20creating%20more%20jobs%20in%202026%2C%20according%20to%20an%20annual%20outlook%20survey%20conducted%20by%20advisory%20firm%20Teneo%20released%20this%20month.%20Sixty-seven%20percent%20of%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECEOs%20surveyed%20said%20they%20expect%20AI%20to%20increase%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fentry-level-jobs-experience-younger-workers-gen-z-employment-careers-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eentry-level%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202026%2C%20and%2058%25%20said%20they%20plan%20to%20add%20senior-leadership%20roles%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20firms%20are%20ramping%20up%20hiring%20in%20engineering%20and%20AI-related%20roles.%20Many%20existing%20jobs%20are%20being%20reconfigured%20or%20reassigned%20as%20certain%20tasks%20become%20increasingly%20automated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%2C%20conducted%20between%20October%2014%20and%20November%2010%2C%20gathered%20responses%20from%20more%20than%20350%20global%20CEOs%20leading%20public%20companies%20with%20at%20least%20%241%20billion%20in%20annual%20revenue%2C%20as%20well%20as%20about%20400%20institutional%20investors%20representing%20%2419%20trillion%20in%20portfolio%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20run%20counter%20to%20the%20prevailing%20narrative%20that%20AI%20is%20automating%20entire%20jobs%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20AI%20is%20wiping%20out%20the%20workforce%20today%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20reshaping%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ryan%20Cox%2C%20Teneo's%20global%20head%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hiring%20momentum%20mirrors%20a%20broader%20surge%20in%20corporate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-finally-paying-ai-cio-survey-2025-12%5C%22%20targe