.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20words%20of%20Taylor%20Swift%2C%20however%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-mainstream-google-traffic-stock-revenue-human-users-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20very%20much%20like%20to%20be%20excluded%20from%20this%20narrative%20because%2C%20it%20says%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20social%20media%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20made%20the%20argument%20in%20a%20lawsuit%20it%20filed%20against%20the%20Commonwealth%20of%20Australia%20and%20its%20Minister%20of%20Communications%20on%20Friday.%20The%20Australian%20law%20is%20meant%20to%20protect%20young%20people%20from%20what%20it%20says%20are%20the%20harmful%20and%20addictive%20effects%20of%20social%20media%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20is%20seeking%20to%20overturn%20the%20country's%20new%20law%2C%20which%20it%20says%20%26quot%3Binfringes%20the%20implied%20freedom%20of%20political%20communication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20legal%20filing%2C%20Reddit%20also%20pushed%20back%20at%20being%20labeled%20an%20%26quot%3Bage-restricted%20social%20media%20platform%26quot%3B%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20Australia's%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Reddit%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Boperates%20as%20a%20collection%20of%20public%20fora%20arranged%20by%20subject.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20because%20it%20is%20not%20the%20case%20that%20the%20sole%20purpose%2C%20or%20a%20significant%20purpose%2C%20of%20Reddit%20is%20to%20enable%20'online%20social%20interaction'%20between%20two%20or%20more%20end-users%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20its%2012-page%20legal%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20added%20that%2C%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20users%20don't%20know%20each%20other's%20real%20identities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReddit%20does%20not%20import%20contact%20lists%20or%20address%20books.%20The%20'upvote%2Fdownvote'%20functionality%20enables%20users%20to%20indicate%20how%20helpful%20they%20found%20the%20information%20that%20was%20posted%20by%20an%20end-user%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20the%20lawsuit.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20intended%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20way%20for%20users%20to%20express%20any%20view%20about%20the%20poster%20themselves.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20Reddit%20is%20significantly%20different%20from%20other%20sites%20that%20allow%20for%20users%20to%20become%20'friends'%20with%20one%20another%2C%20or%20to%20post%20photos%20about%20themselves%2C%20or%20to%20organise%20events.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%2C%20founded%20in%202005%2C%20allows%20users%20to%20post%20and%20reply%20to%20those%20posts%20on%20%26quot%3Bsubreddits%26quot%3B%20dedicated%20to%20almost%20any%20topic%20imaginable.%20Users%20have%20the%20option%20to%20upvote%20or%20downvote%20posts%20and%20can%20send%20each%20other%20direct%20messages.%20While%20Reddit%20users%20can%20use%20their%20real%20names%2C%20most%20of%20them%20operate%20anonymously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20went%20public%20in%202024%20with%20a%20valuation%20of%20%246.4%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20elaborated%20on%20its%20argument%20in%20a%20statement%20addressed%20to%20its%20users%2C%20which%20was%20shared%20on%20the%20platform%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20law%20is%20applied%20to%20Reddit%20inaccurately%2C%20since%20we're%20a%20forum%20primarily%20for%20adults%20and%20we%20don't%20have%20the%20traditional%20social%20media%20features%20the%20government%20has%20taken%20issue%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustralia's%20new%20law%2C%20which%20would%20place%20the%20onus%20on%20social%20media%20platforms%20to%20verify%20users'%20ages%2C%20has%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20other%20companies%20it%20targets%20as%20well%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-app-online-website-video-sharing-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok's%20parent%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ByteDance%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20owns%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%2C%20which%20says%20it%20is%20complying%20with%20the%20law%2C%20told%20its%20users%20that%20doing%20so%20could%20have%20unintended%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20law%20has%20the%20unfortunate%20effect%20of%20forcing%20intrusive%20and%20potentially%20insecure%20verification%20processes%20on%20adults%20as%20well%20as%20minors%2C%20isolating%20teens%20from%20the%20ability%20to%20engage%20in%20age-appropriate%20community%20experiences%20(including%20political%20discussions)%2C%20and%20creating%20an%20illogical%20patchwork%20of%20which%20platforms%20are%20included%20and%20which%20aren't%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustralia%20isn't%20the%20only%20country%20considering%20restricting%20social%20media%20use%20among%20young%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMalaysia%20plans%20to%20ban%20children%20under%2016%20from%20having%20social%20media%20accounts%20in%202026.%20In%20Norway%20and%20Denmark%2C%C2%A0lawmakers%20have%20proposed%20laws%20that%20would%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorway-ban-social-media-kids-under-15-backfire-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eban%20social%20media%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20children%20under%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20handful%20of%20US%20senators%20earlier%20this%20year%20introduced%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustralia-tiktok-instagram-ban-usa-kids-off-social-media-bill-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKids%20Off%20Social%20Media%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20bar%20social%20media%20platforms%20from%20allowing%20children%20under%2013%20years%20old%20to%20create%20or%20maintain%20accounts.%20The%20act%20would%20also%20bar%20platforms%20from%20using%20algorithms%20to%20target%20children